"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"## New Here?\\n\\n**Ambassadors** are ‚Äú[IRL](https://www.howtogeek.com/449518/what-does-irl-mean-and-how-do-you-use-it/)‚Äù [Collaborators](https://mirror.xyz/0xe2A039aB83dB1ea76842FEc23611806d50C4B4Ae/onyNgQAi-2VKGNTDGYK9vf20AK-k7i-3qot58G4Qo54) who represent Mundo Lingo and connect participants during our events. They are collectively responsible for the well-being of Mundo Lingo, holding Managers and Admins accountable for their policies and actions.\\n\\n## Apply\\n\\nJoin [Mundo Lingo Collaborators](https://mirror.xyz/0xe2A039aB83dB1ea76842FEc23611806d50C4B4Ae/onyNgQAi-2VKGNTDGYK9vf20AK-k7i-3qot58G4Qo54) and let group members know you wish to be an Ambassador for your city. If successful you will be given residency in your local [Embassy](https://mirror.xyz/0xe2A039aB83dB1ea76842FEc23611806d50C4B4Ae/GUZj246f3hBt927EWv_XtirgExr-3Xm97nI8nak8BY0).\\n\\n**Already an Ambassador? Continue below‚Ä¶**\\n\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Represent!\\n\\n![](https://images.mirror-media.xyz/publication-images/kcFl83oerIQvGu7ERPgzs.png?height=377&width=659)\\n\\nOn arrival at Mundo Lingo get your **Ambassador flag** (don‚Äôt wait to be offered, ask) along with your usual language flags. Your Ambassador flag should go at the top of your chest above the others. If you don‚Äôt have the flag you‚Äôre not an Ambassador.\\n\\n## Your Mission\\n\\nThere are many ways Ambassadors contribute to Mundo Lingo, but this one unites us all in our #1 objective. When we see someone who looks nervous, shy or alone, we approach them and make them our friend. That‚Äôs all most people need; one friendly face in the social space, and they have all the confidence they need in order to connect with other people knowing that they are not alone.\\n\\n![](https://images.mirror-media.xyz/publication-images/bP9HiT0ixchtmkhZU_qtY.png?height=272&width=419)\\n\\n### The Shy, the Unique and the Specials:\\n\\nAs a community we embrace the specials and the weirdos. The autistic, introverted, extroverted, insecure, nervous, narcissistic, aggressive, any people who face none-spoken rejection on a daily basis. We offer a safe space for people to come and be who they are, to open their butterfly wings without the scornful judgement of the unforgiving conformist societies we live in. It may not be easy but we find the way to understand them and work with them to strengthen their social skills. We know now, that these unique characters often are most interesting, intelligent and beautiful personalities to frequent our events and even fill the ranks of our Ambassador teams.\\n\\nDon‚Äôt fear them, instead, engage and support them. Keep this idea with you. Force yourself to go and talk to that ‚Äòweirdo‚Äô in the corner. You may unleash a very special social butterfly.\\n\\n## The Cupids and the Vultures Hunters\\n\\nThere are 2 prominent types of Ambassadors. Cupids and the Vulture Hunters.**Cupids** unite participants according to their languages or other interests. **Vulture Hunters** are a nightmare if you‚Äôre plan was to get a one-night-stand tonight.\\n\\nIf you‚Äôre a Cupid, [check this out](https://mirror.xyz/0xe2A039aB83dB1ea76842FEc23611806d50C4B4Ae/sKQAXOKMUR7ruynT8iHu8IuCxI9kruvjl0cWp75AROI) üèπ\\n\\nIf you‚Äôre a Vulture Hunter, [check this out](https://mirror.xyz/0xe2A039aB83dB1ea76842FEc23611806d50C4B4Ae/kQBwhQlTdsO8KCXfgG3OJn_ej4pmC5ZUCfOlrKvzIsM) üèπ\\n\\n### üì± Cell Phone Jockeys\\n\\nWhen someone is stood alone glued to their phone it‚Äôs a classic cry for help‚Ä¶ because they‚Äôre shy‚Ä¶ Probably they want to talk but they‚Äôre just scared of facing the social confrontation. Approach them and see if they‚Äôre open to chat with you. If they put their phone away quickly it confirms they welcome the interaction.\\n\\n### Flags on arms\\n\\n![Once once person does it, often others copy](https://images.mirror-media.xyz/publication-images/oM18tspi_VmD_pSTBHGIt.png?height=440&width=857)\\n\\nSometimes participants put the flags on their arms. Sometimes they say it‚Äôs because of the material, but usually it‚Äôs not (often the material on their arm is the same as on their chest). If you see flags on arms, gently suggest they put them on their chest as a courtesy to our other guests, because:\\n\\n**On the chest is**\\n\\n1. Easy for guests to see.\\n2. Good for photographs\\n3. Good for our host bar\\n\\n### Keep going!\\n\\nReady to go above and beyond to support ML in your city? The community will already be grateful to you for fulfilling the roles described in this page. However, if you can do more, there‚Äôs so much more that‚Äôs possible. How about running satellite events, or even leading your team for example? Check out the other Ambassador guides for more information.\\n\\n## Now what?\\n\\nNext up, how to be a perfect [Cupid](https://mirror.xyz/0xe2A039aB83dB1ea76842FEc23611806d50C4B4Ae/sKQAXOKMUR7ruynT8iHu8IuCxI9kruvjl0cWp75AROI)\\n\\n### Go Back\\n\\nüëà [Welcome Collaborators](https://mirror.xyz/0xe2A039aB83dB1ea76842FEc23611806d50C4B4Ae/onyNgQAi-2VKGNTDGYK9vf20AK-k7i-3qot58G4Qo54)\",\"timestamp\":1639558732,\"title\":\"Welcome Ambassadors!\"},\"digest\":\"Z-nj0eYpG0CuhTrhfrbTOGMa8PFGCRwFHY4NpRi2JH4\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0xe2A039aB83dB1ea76842FEc23611806d50C4B4Ae\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"34suyCfnLUoFM02SOhmJJJ9iXgiiL5kC6iPH6Fv3LXk\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"jtVAiplEVAd0RPMj7L2P0umm9wTPdvk-kh1vAJTvwJc\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"APRDdJ9uOONyMGVRV-nGHG2RcPspxEEECTVMEAkWGjE2CFTH1w07oTd4y721vspja_MY75YWNDnSi6OYQxn04w\",\"signingKeySignature\":\"0x57d0f7cbea22222afabed23e09ac819f759269ea4cca2a83cdd992ddf3ffe88d22a7afd325b70c3c1ae7dee6f5fc8e22188ba69c589cf1f0528e258261121ae51b\",\"signingKeyMessage\":\"I authorize publishing on mirror.xyz from this device using:\\n{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"34suyCfnLUoFM02SOh